<bioghist altrender="history" encodinganalog="545" id="a2">
	<head>Historical Note</head>
<p>
Darien, Fairfield County, Town established in May 1820, Parent Town: Stamford
</p>
<p>
The Darien Probate District was constituted May 18, 1921, from the Stamford Probate District and merged on January 5, 2011 with the New Canaan Probate District to create the Darien – New Canaan Probate District. The Darien – New Canaan Probate District serves the municipalities of Darien and New Canaan.
</p>
<p> 
Town of Darien, Probate District chronology:<lb/> 
May 1820 – May 17, 1921, Stamford District<lb/>
May 18, 1921 – January 4, 2011, Darien District<lb/>
January 5, 2011 – Present, Darien – New Canaan District<lb/>
</p>

<p>For Probate Court contact information and hours of operation see, <extptr linktype="simple" href="http://www.ctprobate.gov/Pages/Directory.aspx" show="replace" actuate="onrequest" title="Probate Court Directory"/>.</p> 

</bioghist>



<scopecontent encodinganalog="520" id="a3">
	<head>Scope and Content</head>
	<p>Bond record books, 1925-1849. These volumes are copies that were created from the original record books by the Darien Probate Court.</p>
	<p>Probate record books other than bonds, None. Contact the probate court to access original record books.</p>
	<p>Probate files, None. Contact the probate court to access original files.</p>
</scopecontent> 

<arrangement encodinganalog="351$b" id="a5">
	<head>Arrangement</head>
	<p>The first volume of the bond record books is designated A, followed by Volumes 1-3. Volumes 1 and 2 are in 2 parts each.</p>
</arrangement>




